xel Ring — Status LED Array for System Feedback#ESP32 3.3V Compatibility Issue#{13}":[127,127],"#WS2812B NeoPixel Ring — Status LED Array for System Feedback#ESP32 3.3V Compatibility Issue#{14}":[128,129]},"outlinks":[{"title":"displays","target":"displays","line":3},{"title":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","target":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","line":17},{"title":"arduino-nano-v3-is-a-22-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-mini-usb","target":"arduino-nano-v3-is-a-22-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-mini-usb","line":17},{"title":"arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b","target":"arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b","line":17},{"title":"dccduino-nano-is-an-arduino-nano-clone-with-ch340-usb","target":"dccduino-nano-is-an-arduino-nano-clone-with-ch340-usb","line":17},{"title":"elegoo-mega-2560-r3-is-an-arduino-mega-clone-with-ch340-usb","target":"elegoo-mega-2560-r3-is-an-arduino-mega-clone-with-ch340-usb","line":17},{"title":"nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3","target":"nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3","line":17},{"title":"osepp-uno-r3-plus-is-an-arduino-uno-clone-at-5v","target":"osepp-uno-r3-plus-is-an-arduino-uno-clone-at-5v","line":17},{"title":"txs0108e-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-auto-direction","target":"txs0108e-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-auto-direction","line":112},{"title":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","target":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","line":119},{"title":"arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b","target":"arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b","line":120},{"title":"arduino-nano-v3-is-a-22-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-mini-usb","target":"arduino-nano-v3-is-a-22-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-mini-usb","line":121},{"title":"elegoo-mega-2560-r3-is-an-arduino-mega-clone-with-ch340-usb","target":"elegoo-mega-2560-r3-is-an-arduino-mega-clone-with-ch340-usb","line":122},{"title":"nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3","target":"nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3","line":123},{"title":"txs0108e-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-auto-direction","target":"txs0108e-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-auto-direction","line":124},{"title":"hw-221-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-bss138-based","target":"hw-221-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-bss138-based","line":125},{"title":"displays","target":"displays","line":128}],"metadata":{"description":"WS2812B addressable RGB LED ring for rover status indication — each LED individually controllable via single data pin. 5V, 60mA max per LED (all white full brightness). Color-coded system status: green=ready, red=fault, blue=GPS lock, etc.","topics":["[[displays]]"],"status":"needs-test","quantity":1,"voltage":[5],"interfaces":["Digital"],"logic_level":"5V (data pin needs 5V logic for reliable operation — use level shifter from 3.3V MCUs)","manufacturer":"WorldSemi / Generic","part_number":"WS2812B","pinout":"NeoPixel Ring (3 connections):\n5V   → 5V power (dedicated supply recommended for >8 LEDs)\nGND  → Ground (common with MCU ground)\nDIN  → Data input (from MCU GPIO)\nDOUT → Data output (to next LED in chain, if daisy-chaining)\n","compatible_with":["[[arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts]]","[[nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3]]","[[elegoo-mega-2560-r3-is-an-arduino-mega-clone-with-ch340-usb]]","[[arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b]]","[[arduino-nano-v3-is-a-22-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-mini-usb]]","[[dccduino-nano-is-an-arduino-nano-clone-with-ch340-usb]]","[[osepp-uno-r3-plus-is-an-arduino-uno-clone-at-5v]]"],"used_in":[],"warnings":["60mA per LED at full white brightness — 8 LEDs = 480mA, 16 LEDs = 960mA. Use dedicated 5V supply for larger rings, do NOT power from Arduino 5V pin","Add a 300-500 ohm resistor on the data line (between MCU pin and DIN) to prevent signal reflections","Add a 1000uF electrolytic capacitor across 5V and GND near the ring to absorb power supply surges","3.3V data signal from ESP32 is technically out of spec for WS2812B (needs >3.5V for logic HIGH at 5V supply) — works sometimes but unreliable. Use a level shifter or run LEDs at 3.3V (dimmer)","First LED in chain handles timing — if it dies, the entire chain goes dark"],"datasheet_url":""},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[[65,70],[79,105]],"key":"docs/parts/ws2812b-neopixel-ring-status-led-array-for-system-feedback.md"},"smart_blocks:docs/parts/ws2812b-neopixel-ring-status-led-array-for-system-feedback.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"v7ndo7","at":1776210732638},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.04646945,-0.00742171,0.01584255,-0.00952631,-0.03448237,0.01719953,-0.02143516,0.06287903,-0.01786227,0.0844616,0.0194175,-0.06365833,0.02274827,0.06759914,-0.00369632,-0.03947647,0.0356995,0.00193066,0.03090276,0.00919298,0.05639369,-0.06447037,-0.01336038,0.00657213,0.0265885,0.07061439,0.00773216,-0.03371238,-0.07682417,-0.24141529,-0.02210787,0.01859353,0.01595442,-0.02464186,-0.00956289,-0.06856107,-0.00859587,-0.02770263,-0.04093534,-0.0025234,0.06593473,-0.06489164,0.03894068,0.01401376,-0.03455365,-0.04100233,-0.06765312,-0.03391185,0.00856578,-0.06955197,0.03109321,-0.04418677,0.03721192,-0.04026493,0.05001961,0.09479214,0.032285,0.09288109,0.09667068,0.01043929,0.04976252,0.08547568,-0.1758464,0.09032732,0.06251545,0.02113046,-0.04643648,-0.04819815,0.02501074,-0.00334736,0.04496966,-0.03675794,0.01806237,0.04406492,-0.04788975,-0.01736324,0.04847268,-0.07599483,-0.00438215,-0.00100823,-0.02308359,0.07270395,-0.05964176,0.04552675,0.01683027,-0.00486643,-0.03178176,0.0604964,-0.03370666,0.03786216,-0.04124718,-0.06094434,-0.00156897,-0.02390633,-0.05184801,-0.02419748,0